cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.DS 

This paper deals with structured prediction, which is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the category of supervised learning. The paper proposes an extension of SparseMAP, a differentiable method for structured prediction, which is relevant to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also uses factor graphs, a graphical model commonly used in natural language processing and computer vision, which makes it relevant to the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper presents experiments on three structured prediction tasks, which suggests that it could also be relevant to the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
